RICHARDS BAY - A senior KwaZulu-Natal politician has condemned the murder of a Jozini local municipality councillor.
	
	Njabulo Dlamini was stabbed to death on Monday in Richards Bay while on holiday. The motive for the killing is not known. READ: ANC KZN considering providing security for its councillors KZN Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs MEC, Nomusa Dube-Ncube, has urged police to act quickly and arrest the perpetrators. Last year, about five councillors were killed in KwaZulu-Natal. eNCA